President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Patrick K. Nakamura as a member of the Federal Mine Safety and Health Review Commission. He has also announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts, including Jeri L. Williams as a member of the Medal of Valor Review Board, Phil Fuentes as a member of the President's Advisory Commission on Educational Excellence for Hispanics, Charles H. Ramsey and Dan Tangherlini as members of the National Infrastructure Advisory Council, Thelma Duggin and David C. Jacobson as members of the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars, Tom A. Bernstein, David Marchick, Michael Polsky, Richard Price, and Ronald A. Ratner as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council.